<br>
I don't.<br>
<br>
Everyone wanting lists and schedules please get over it.<br>
<br>
Want to group somewhere ? Find a zone (yourself) see who's there (yourself) LFG (yourself) or /tell your friends and ask them to come (yourself).<br>
<br>
Why must everyone need everything handed to them ? Already, hell levels have been removed, so everyone under 50 has been handed several levels worth of xp already. Then newb quest armor is added. I remember buying a combine Scimitar so I could have magic slash and wearing my own patchwork armor. Again, something handed to them.<br>
<br>
Want a raid ? Here are some suggestions.<br>
<br>
1) Make friends and organize one. Don't sit on your hands waiting for some guild to let you tag along.<br>
<br>
2) Form a guild, organize raids, and understand why you don't want tagalongs.<br>
<br>
3) Join a guild that raids and knows what they are doing.<br>
<br>
4) Make a Druid, port for cash, buy your stuff.<br>
<br>
Why grind ?<br>
<br>
With level come a few things..experience, hit points, AC, Resists, armor (useable by level) and personal skill. If you don't have it..take a look at whats out there, and then get some of it.<br>
<br>
Enough pretend irony, enough feigned insult, enough uber-hate. If you don't strive to be the best at whatever you do its noones fault of your own that you may or may not suck.<br>
It is possible to experience high-end content in this game and still have fun.<br>
<br>
As for raids being limited to the 55+ people. They aren't at all.<br>
BUT, they are a hell of alot more fun when the risk/reward is high and you can actually contribute more than just being a mana sink.<br>
<br>
