<br>
There's quite a bit of hostility around here. It doesn't seem the least bit warranted.<br>
<br>
Clearly a list/schedule isn't going to work on Rodcet with strong guilds opposed to it.<br>
<br>
It's equally clear to me that it is working on Brell.<br>
<br>
That's fine - different strokes for different folks. On Brell I'll appreciate the real-life convenience of *knowing* that I'll be raiding Fear next Tuesday. On Rodcet I'll play it by ear.<br>
<br>
I've got no reason to accuse anyone else of wanting things handed to them, or lack of effort, or whining, or newbieness, or imply that they have gotten undeserved xp, or begging, or to laugh at anyone. Nor have I done those things.<br>
<br>
Lighten up.<br>
<br>
To go back to ktadema's original post - looks like you're not going to see a calendar. You might be able to get around to the message boards of some guilds (see Guild Links forum) and see if they have upcoming events listed - there are some who occasionally allow strangers to tag along. Some points made here are valid, sometimes it turns out disastrous, but more often in my experience the extras do blend in without serious trouble. Certainly some guilds will not have their upcoming events viewable by the public, and that's fine. (Someone will post that it's &quot;stupid&quot; to have it public viewable, and he's entitled to his opinion - but I won't always agree with it.)<br>
<br>
<br>
