<br>
What I meant by work is.  This game is designed to provide challanges.  To over come them you have to work at it.  Being as how this is not a single player game and that there's thousands of other real people in the game with you at any time, one of those challanges is having to deal with the schedules of other people.  Not to mention simply learning how to handle the encounter(s) your attempting.<br>
<br>
There's a lot of things in this world that I do for fun, that require work.  I like to shoot pool.  But I wasn't very good when I first started playing.  I had to work at it to keep from getting humiliated every time I played.  I like to play football on occasion.  I need to work at keeping in shape so that I'm not out of breath running 30 feet.  I like to play everquest.  I have to work at my leveling, and keeping in touch with other guilds/people to find out what they're doing so that I can either a) not step on thier toes or b) plan around them.<br>
<br>
I don't find every little thing in EQ to be fun.  But the enjoyment I do take from the game is worth the work I put into it.  For me at least.<br>
